FORMAT: 1A
HOST: http://127.0.0.1:5000

# Library API - API Blueprint

Small library management API for comparison demo.

# Group Books

## Books Collection [/api/v1/books]

### Get all books [GET]

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
          "data": [
            {
              "id": 1,
              "title": "Clean Code",
              "author": "Robert C. Martin"
            }
          ]
        }

### Create a new book [POST]

+ Request (application/json)

        {
          "title": "Domain-Driven Design",
          "author": "Eric Evans"
        }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

        {
          "id": 3,
          "title": "Domain-Driven Design",
          "author": "Eric Evans"
        }

+ Response 400 (application/json)

        {
          "error": "title and author are required"
        }

## Book [/api/v1/books/{book_id}]

+ Parameters
    + book_id: 1 (number, required) - Book id

### Get book by id [GET]

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
          "id": 1,
          "title": "Clean Code",
          "author": "Robert C. Martin"
        }

+ Response 404 (application/json)

        {
          "error": "Not found"
        }

### Update book by id [PUT]

+ Request (application/json)

        {
          "title": "Clean Architecture",
          "author": "Robert C. Martin"
        }

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
          "id": 1,
          "title": "Clean Architecture",
          "author": "Robert C. Martin"
        }

+ Response 400 (application/json)

        {
          "error": "title and author are required"
        }

+ Response 404 (application/json)

        {
          "error": "Not found"
        }

### Delete book by id [DELETE]

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
          "message": "Deleted"
        }

+ Response 404 (application/json)

        {
          "error": "Not found"
        }
